        <li>Hardy, Robert, <em>Longbow: A Social and Military History</em>, 1977.</li> 
        <li>Examines a common type of foot soldier that was present in Western European armies during this period, although the focus is on England.</li> 
        <li>Hewitt, H.J. , <em>The Horse in Medieval England</em>, 1983.</li> 
        <li>Provides a fine introduction to the Medieval warhorse of Western Europe, one of the most important items used by Medieval warriors of all different periods and cultures (particularly the knight of Western Europe) and yet neglected by writers.</li> 
        <li>Hill. D..R. "Trebuchets," <em>Viator</em> 4 (1973), pp. 99-114.</li> 
        <li>Hyland, Ann, <em>The Medieval Warhorse from Byzantium to the Crusades Stroud</em>: Sutton, 1994.</li> 
        <li>Actually more up-to-date and broader in scope (both are far superior to</li> 
        <li>R.H.C. Davis' flawed study.</li> 
